<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-07-15T11:29:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-07-15T11:29:00-05:00" n="604" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d604">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/2304</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Archangel</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CF1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Cole</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Archangel</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-07-15T21:00:00+04:31"><hi rend="italic">July 15,
                                            1918, 9 p.m.</hi></date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received July 20, 12.08
                                    p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>77. The attitude of the inhabitants of Archangel in anticipation of
                                the arrival of the Allied forces as follows: (1) Welcome on the part
                                of civilians; (2) publicly expressed disfavor toward military
                                intervention by the local Bolshevik leaders goaded thereto by
                                Moscow; (3) part of the Archangel executive department would
                                nevertheless eventually cooperate as well as welcome the Allies, if
                                they proceed with tact, luring rather than bullying.</p>
                            <p>My cipher telegrams in Russia will not be accepted except diplomatics
                                to the Department.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_CF1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Cole</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>